$ Avaloq: users

Users apparently don't belong the the → Companies-Products/Avaloq/object/model[object model].

{ User types #avq-user-types

  Operational users: users who use Avaloq for operational work (think executing → Companies-Products/Avaloq/order/workflow[workflow] actions).
  Such a user needs to be licensed.

  → Companies-Products/Avaloq/users/role[Roles]: A role is a set of *access rights*. Roles can hierarchically be assigned other roles and finally users. A role needs not be licensed.

  Technical users: are used to run → Companies-Products/Avaloq/BGP[background processes].
  -
  Usually, their name starts with a `#` (for example `#EOD`).
  -
  Surprisingly, technically users need not be licensed.

  Customisation users.

  Virtual users. They're used to trace → Companies-Products/Avaloq/order[orders] (often used for e-Banking users).
  -
  The virtual user for a session can be set with the session → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/DDIC: `session.set_virt_user(…)`.
  
  See also table → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/tables/code/user/type.

}
{ API

  Users are created or modified with → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/plsql-packages/migr_user[`migr_user#`].

}
